elling story for centuries-and one that will captivate students and scholars today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aIndians of MexicoxHistoryy16th century. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / Mexico.2bisacsh1 aBenton, Bradley, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBrian, Amber, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGarcía Loaeza, Pablo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311074525240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271072067?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271072067423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271072067/original  a978-3-11-074525-2  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK